i think the wording could be changed instead of having a list

Obviously
I was just positing that it feels weird

Players choose a legendary creature as the “Commander” for their deck. Details

Players choose a card in which one of its sides is legendary creature as the “Commander” for their deck.
I'm sure there are other cards you find 'out of theme' that are already legal...
and by theme, which theme do you mean?

RC sculpts the format to evoke a specific flavor. Legendary creatures facilitate the Singleton nature of the deck. Deckbuilding restrictions per your commander’s color are constructed to make it feel like your commander is literally offended by things outside its color identity. That’s why you couldn’t create other-colored mana for so long. It’s why you still can’t use hybrid cards with only half of your commander’s color.  They craft rules to create a theme of an actual commander in charge of an army, that you’re allowed to help lead. Jushi Apprentice feels outside of that theme because it isn’t a fully-fledged commander yet. 
I don’t despise the idea, I just think exceptions are weird. If they’re going to make exceptions I’d rather they just go whole-hog
@don I’m down to help.
It's the same with [[Elbrus]], you can't run it as a commander despite it being able to become a legendary creature.
